    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The nationality, culture, or style of the Hakka people, an ethnic group of China, considered to be a branch of the Han. Originally from North China, but migrated to South China (especially Guangdong, Fujian, Jiangxi, and Guangxi provinces) during the fall of the Nan (Southern) Song dynasty in the 1270s.</Note_Text>
